---
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Anchor components, Jeff Mills"
  description="Architectural overview of the Anchor component library: Vue 2 SFCs compiled to custom elements, with the directive and slot patterns that later became Meridian."
>
  <p class="project-back"><a href="/projects/anchor">&laquo; back to anchor</a></p>
  <h1 class="page-title">anchor · component library</h1>
  <p class="project-meta">
    <span class="project-year">2018-2022</span>
    <span class="meta-sep">&middot;</span>
    <span class="project-status">proprietary</span>
    <span class="meta-sep">&middot;</span>
    <span>~100 components</span>
    <span class="meta-sep">&middot;</span>
    <span>vue 2 SFCs</span>
  </p>

  <p class="page-lede">
    Roughly a hundred Vue 2 components across the two iterations of
    Anchor. Coverage spans forms, charts, modals, navigation, content
    layouts, video, and media-player wrappers. Notes on the patterns
    used across the library below.
  </p>

  <aside class="callout">
    <span class="callout-label">Architectural overview only</span>
    <p>
      Component source stays in the private repository. The patterns and
      architecture are described below. Happy to walk through component
      implementations under NDA,
      <a href="mailto:jeffy9@gmail.com">reach out</a>.
    </p>
  </aside>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <h2 class="section-title">patterns you'll see across the library</h2>
  <ul class="proof-list">
    <li>
      <strong>JSDoc on every prop.</strong> Storybook&rsquo;s
      <code>vue-docgen</code> integration parsed these into Controls,
      Args, and docs pages automatically. Documentation was structural,
      not optional.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Polymorphic rendering.</strong> Common components (Button,
      Card, Hero) decide between <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> and
      <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> (or other host elements) based on a
      prop, so the same component covers the common variants without a
      separate &ldquo;LinkButton.&rdquo;
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Slot composition.</strong> Most components default to text
      props for the common case and expose named slots for advanced
      use. Buttons, modals, tooltips, cards, same shape.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>WCAG-cited a11y comments.</strong> Accessibility
      requirements live next to the props they apply to, with WCAG
      success criterion numbers (1.1.1, 2.4.6) inline.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Async-imported nested components</strong> via
      <code>webpackChunkName</code> hints so the bundle stays
      tree-shakeable across composition. Icons stay out of the Button
      bundle unless actually rendered.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Custom directives instead of mixins</strong>
      (intersect, bounds, drawer) when the behavior was DOM-y rather than
      data-y. Composition without component bloat.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Length-aware tooltip rendering.</strong> The tooltip
      component switches between a positioned bubble and a modal based
      on message length, so the same API covers short hints and long
      explanatory copy without consumers having to choose.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <p class="project-foot">
    Back to <a href="/projects/anchor">Anchor overview</a>
    &middot; Compare to <a href="/projects/meridian/components">Meridian components</a>
  </p>
</Base>

